    <div class="card">
        <h3>💰 Budgeting & Finance</h3>
        <p>
            Managing money is one of the biggest challenges students face. Rent, food, transport, and daily spending can build up quickly.
        </p>

        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1554224155-6726b3ff858f" />

        <h4>Useful Tools</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="https://monzo.com" target="_blank">Monzo</a> – A mobile banking app that allows you to track spending in real time.
                You can set monthly budgets, get notifications when you spend money, and see exactly where your money is going.
                This helps students avoid overspending and stay in control of their finances.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://emma-app.com" target="_blank">Emma</a> – Connects multiple bank accounts in one place.
                It automatically categorises your spending (e.g. food, bills, subscriptions) so you can see patterns.
                This is useful for spotting unnecessary expenses and saving money.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://mint.intuit.com" target="_blank">Mint</a> – A budgeting tool that helps plan long-term finances.
                You can set goals (like saving for rent or travel) and track progress over time.
                This helps students build better financial habits.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            MMU offers financial support including hardship funds and advice services to help students manage their money.
        </p>

        <a href="https://www.mmu.ac.uk/about-us/contact" target="_blank" class="btn">
     Contact Us to find out more 
</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>📅 Time Management</h3>
        <p>
            Staying organised is essential for keeping up with university work. Planning your time properly can reduce stress.
        </p>

        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506784983877-45594efa4cbe" />

        <h4>Useful Tools</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="https://calendar.google.com" target="_blank">Google Calendar</a> – Allows you to schedule lectures, deadlines, and personal events.
                You can set reminders so you never miss important dates, helping you stay organised throughout the semester.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://trello.com" target="_blank">Trello</a> – A visual task management tool using boards and cards.
                You can break assignments into smaller tasks and move them as you progress, making big projects easier to manage.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.notion.so" target="_blank">Notion</a> – An all-in-one workspace for notes, tasks, and planning.
                Students can create study plans, organise notes, and track deadlines in one place.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            MMU provides workshops and academic support to help improve time management skills.
        </p>

        <a href="https://www.mmu.ac.uk/about-us/contact" class="btn">Contact Us To Find Out More</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>📚 Study Support</h3>
        <p>
            Using the right study techniques can make a big difference in your results.
        </p>

        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1513258496099-48168024aec0" />

        <h4>Useful Tools</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="https://quizlet.com" target="_blank">Quizlet</a> – Helps you create flashcards and quizzes.
                This is useful for revising key terms and testing your knowledge before exams.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://grammarly.com" target="_blank">Grammarly</a> – A writing assistant that checks grammar and spelling.
                It also improves clarity, helping students submit higher-quality assignments.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.forestapp.cc" target="_blank">Forest</a> – A focus app that encourages you to stay off your phone.
                You grow a virtual tree while studying, which helps build better concentration habits.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            MMU offers library services, academic advisors, and study support sessions.
        </p>

         <a href="https://www.mmu.ac.uk/about-us/contact" class="btn">Contact Us To Find Out More</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>🧠 Wellbeing</h3>
        <p>
            Taking care of your mental health is important during university.
        </p>

        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506126613408-eca07ce68773" />

        <h4>Useful Tools</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.headspace.com" target="_blank">Headspace</a> – Offers guided meditation sessions.
                This can help reduce stress, improve focus, and support mental wellbeing.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.calm.com" target="_blank">Calm</a> – Provides sleep stories, breathing exercises, and relaxation tools.
                Useful for managing anxiety and improving sleep quality.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://www.studentminds.org.uk" target="_blank">Student Minds</a> – A student-focused mental health resource.
                Offers advice, support, and guidance specifically for university students.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            MMU provides counselling services, wellbeing advisors, and support teams.
        </p>

         <a href="https://www.mmu.ac.uk/about-us/contact" class="btn">Contact Us To Find Out More</a>
